values:
School in two weeks. AHH. I like just chilling and not worrying about class. Our new townhouse is amazing, pretty big and nice actually. I am happy right now. 

BUT I AM excited for DREW to come back. I don't know what it is, but as soon as I see him it's like instant comfort. Now i wont have to miss him. I FREAKING love him. We went putt-putt and ate fazoli's with Kara and Joe. He got me these gorgeous flowers for my bday,& PF Changs= heaven. Can't wait till school, but we had some awesome times this summer. And I cant wait to visit the UP again, great memories. 

Work is so boring I could shoot myself. Aside from the occasional interesting customer, LAME. I read an entire book today, front to back. HOLY GOD, I get paid for reading? Sometimes I feel cheesy for reading romance and girly novels. Whatever, I'll read a biography or something to balance it out. 

My birthday was fantastic. More like a week of fun. My friends here made it amazing. We had a party here on Saturday. I am really lucky to know such wonderful people. Seeing old friends was great, and I got an ice cream cake, balloons and everything. Amazing. <3 u guys. 


I feel really boring. I dont know if its work, or that its 11pm and I'm tired. Oh well, goodnight.
im so in love its ridiculous.

Its already near the end of July. Thats crazy madness. In 2 weeks I can move into my apartment. I am excited, but at the same time for some reason right now I'm comfortable. Oh well. It will be really fun to decorate a new room and stuff.

I took an entire wk off from work. I went to see Drew in the UP again, and to family vaca in Pentwater. Drew's was really great. I got to meet some more of his friends, and hang out with his mom a bit. It's weird to feel so close to someone, after spending time with their mom. hah. We went to the beach a ton, and partied it up. ALSO, I went to Red Lobster for the first time! And we stayed at our hotel, so that was good. It was a wonderful time, and I can NOT wait to see him again. Cuddling=best ever. My family rented a house in Pentwater. It was super duper nice, and 2 mins from the beach. It was a great wk to relax. 

I saw Wedding Crashers, it was real funny. Also this wk end, I went over to Amy's and we dressed up in 80's clothes and did our hair huge and in scrunchies. lol how random? good times. 



im le tired. workin 830-530 tmmrw. Night kids.

<3<3<3

JULY 5th. wowzers. Fun wk end in grand haven.. Some funny funnny times and quotes. mostly from hutch. 

"I need to get some double huge batteries"
"The sun like, lights up the whole world"
"EVERYThing real big"
"CUTERS, hotters, roxers, hutchers.. etc"

gotta love, waking up at 6am, wearing the exact same s.suit as ur friend AND 10000 other ppl. sand in ur pringles, red bull, drunken escapades, amy wanting to streak at a retirement place, would u rather, 4 girls in 1 big bed, mcd's breakfast in bed, fireworks in the pouring rain, gettin uber burnt, hitting a huge boulder with the mini van, good times. 


ahh and then i only work 3 more days, and off to the UP to see my baby, then to pentwater for a family vaca. good times ahead. YAY. I can NOT wait, i dont know why but i miss drucks more than anything.


xoxo much love.

Summer is going ok thus far. Not too exciting or boring. 

My Organic Chem class is over with on Tuesday, I have never been so happy in my life to pass a class. I only have to get 40/220 pts to pass... so lets all pray that's easy. We went to Canada a few wk ends ago for Dianas bday. It was crazy fun. IT felt like Florida b/c it was so hot, but there was soo many ppl it was ridic. It is a great feeling to drink in front of cops without the risk of bein in trouble. 

I went camping in Traverse City with Drew! It was ridiculously fun. Everytime I get to see him I am soo happy, and everytime I leave I get all sad. hah. But we just camped and hung out and ate a flippin trillion smores and hot dogs. God, I really do love that boy. He makes me feel tres bien. <3 <3

Other than that, I have been playin on my mom's sball team. It is crazy fun. The ladies are soo funny and sometimes drunk. haha good times. Hopefully when my class is over I can hang out with my friends more! I did get to see Abby and her babies recently though, soo f'in cute. Like, wow. yeah. gorgeous kids.

We are moving into our apartment in a month and a week or so!!! soo excited. I cant wait. At the same time I am not used to having to pay for everything, and it might suck once it all hits me. I am really goin to have to keep track of my money and spend it wisely.

I cant describe how happy I am right now. This wk end was amazing. I met drew at the mackinac bridge friday and we went to dinner, and swam and chilled in the hot tub. Then drove to his house saturday morning. His town is really nice and cute, and the land is amazing. Trees, bays with crystal clear water and cliffs. It was so refreshing. I met his grandparents and some of his friends. Then we went on Sunday to his camp back in the woods. Shot his gun, rode the four wheeler, cooked hot dogs.. It was so.. calming, and felt so right. It was really sad to leave.. but at the same time I am so content right now. I feel so lucky to have him. 


gah. this is the end of me gushing :) sorry. haha

I am in love right now with Howie Day, or maybe it's just his Collide song. meh, whatever. I've been busy at home, with work and class everyday. I guess it's better than being bored all the time. Amy is doing well since her surgery, shes such a trooper. Its amazing really, i love that girl to death. 

I wish I would have had livejournal since I was little, it would've been sweet to write down all the awesome memories. I went and visited Kelly today, she was at her house with Mackayla and Elisha. I love little kids so much, sooo f'in cute. 

About a wk until my mini vacation. God, I hate not seeing drew. It will be the best wk end ever. :D



Love to you all.

So I'm home. Not really anything exciting. I can't believe I won't be in the dorms ever again. Kinda feels awesome though. I can not wait until August. Living with some of my best friends=ROCK ON. So I have to take Organic Chemistry this summer, but only until June 30th.. I hope I can survive.

It's really weird to be away from people. I feel like after this wk end I should be going back to State. It's not so much that I don't like my house, it's that I love campus and everyone on it. I would rather stay there all summer and party like a rock star. 

Im hoping the summer is fun and relaxing, but goes fast. I'm anxious for next yr and all it has to offer me. Trip to the U.P in 3 weeks, I'm already anxious. Weird to care about someone so much.. 


Amy is having her brain surgery next wk. I LOVE YOU GIRL. You will do amazing :) All my love.






happy mothers day. have a good first wk of summer everyone. <3 <3
I don't want to take exams. I don't want to go. I don't want to say goodbye. I don't want to pack up my things. I don't want to leave people I care about. I don't want to miss you.

I cant believe I'm almost a junior in college! How old is that, seriously? It's like 2 more years and then I have to actually start my real life.. Thats the scariest thing ever. Every year it seems impossible that it's happening. That's the one thing that is always consistent in life, change. And it sucks that I hate change. 

On a happy note we wont our IM softball championship game! 3-0, with all mercies! YAY. It's super fun. Makes me miss high school softball..

Sometimes I catch myself worrying about stuff all the time. I have no reason too. It's like the one thing about myself I wish I could change. And sometimes that I hold myself back from saying what I feel..  

The tulips outside the wharton center are awesome. Theres like 5 million all clustered about. I love flowers, I might go cut myself a boquet. haha. 



wow most random entry ever. <3 much love.

My wk end was amazing. Thursday night I had a unique time @ wilson. Haven't got that drunk in awhile. Thanks hutch for listening to me cry, and everyone for making sure I didn't die. Thanks drucks :) Needless to say I woke up with a sore hip (from falling down a ladder), a swollen eyebrow & ring( from falling face first into a door), and crusty eyes (from crying for no reason). ahhh memories. lol Drucks and I went to house sit b/c my parents left for vegas.. really great time. Bike riding, trampoline, breakfast.. Then we watched my sister win her sball tournament! YAY. Last night we went to Starting Line, super super fun. They need to have concerts like that all the time. School seems to not really matter right now, just b/c i have a lot of other things I want to do rather than study. Oh well. 





Is time standing still yet?

In light of playing games @ wilson, I decided to ask you a few would you rather questions.:D

Would you rather: 

Be able to fly or be invisible? (Invisible)
Hit every red light for the rest of your life or always be wrong? (Red Light)
Have to eat a beetle before every meal or never be able to eat a dessert? (Beetle. haha)
Be a meter taller or a meter shorter? (I say shorter, everyone loves midgets)
Shave your head bald or lose your pinky finger for life? (shave my head, i <3 my pinky)
Be in a chamber of 1million giant mosquitoes for a week or wear a poison ivy suit for a month? (mosquitoes)
Live forever or die tommorow? (FOREVER!)
Be the giver or the taker? (giver)
Have cankles or old lady arms? (cankles, OBV!)
Have loved and lost or never loved at all? (loved and lost)
Have feet as hands or hands as feet? (hands as feet! that'd be ridic)
Never be able to use AOL again or your cell phone? ( hmm i REALLY cant choose)



That is all. Not a long time until summer.. dont really know how i feel about it. GAhh If it was a choice to stop time for a month or move ahead a month, i'd stop time. Today it was soo gorgeous outside, the sky was ridiculously blue and the trees are so green. i <3 it.
I don't want to ever stop feeling the way I do right now..

So, pretty much a sweet wk end. Except for the fact that we lost. Michigan State is by far the best campus ever though. Thursday night, wow. Drunkeness at Wilson AGAIN. Its just like routine for me now, I don't even think about what I'm doing Thursday nights. Thats really bad though because I havent went to my Friday class for like 5 times. God sometimes I hate myself for being such a lazy ass. I was doin well in that class too. But Thursday night was ridiculous and included spilling massive amounts of drinks all over everything. Then I remember calling everyone over to tell them "Get er done if she aint been done to git"..or something of the sort.. wtf? lol Also I remember the funny ass elevator ride with Hutch and Tom @ Spartys. Passing out carrots and dip with Drew was also funny. Alcohol rocks. lol.

Last night was fun too. We didn't win the basketball game, but still I had fun. I wanted to go to Stoddard but apparently everyone was getting tear gased.. thats no good at all.. I took it upon myself to drink a whole 1/2 fifth.. hmm. not cool. lame, or lame-o as drew would say. 

Also I got pranked on April Fool's Day and didn't even know it, since I haven't been at my dorm since like Weds. night. Wow.. I should really start staying there more. but ne ways so i go to get some underwear out and im like wtf? I have like zero pairs, and no bras.. I just figured I must've lost a ton of underwear.. Danielle is like, whit do u have ne bras or underwear? wow. good one guys. I didnt even know u hid them all.  i laughed. <3 I can not picture living without you guys..

ok i just have to write this b/c it was funny. Sarah Math was online and was talking to hutch and math goes " I sure wish whitney was on line, I need to know how much smirinoff blue label costs." lmao. WOW, come on guys i dont drink THAT much. haha funny stuff. HAPPY st. patricks day. Also, much love. <3

So I was sitting in the cafe and got all reflective. I actually like sitting there alone and listening to everyone talk.I heard 5 overly tan girls talk about their 'like totally awesome time in Cancun'. Then I heard a boy ramble on to this girl about how a plane engine works.. I'm sure she was thrilled. ;P

I love the feeling I get when I know Drucks is coming over to visit. It really never fails. It seems like after so many times it would just go away.. Yeah, it doesn't.. I think thats a good sign.

I joined the group RUBI.(Respecting and Understanding Body Image). I'm super excited about it. I really want to get involved with it and learn a lot. 

Just ran like 3 miles. I thought it was warmer this morning, yeah it must've gotten cold. It still felt great.. Running is my favorite thing to do.. It's such a personal thing to me, and it's so relaxing.

No matter how many times I've heard it, time really does go by fast.. It's so weird. I wish sometime I could just freeze it and get like an extra day in.. That'd be awesome..

All around the country coast to coast,
people always say what do you like most,
I don't wanna brag i don't wanna boast,
I always tell 'em I like toast.
yeah TOAST yeah TOAST

i get up in the mornin' bout six AM,
have a little jelly have a little jam,
take a piece of bread put it in the slot,
push down the lever and the wires gets hot,
i get toast.

yeah TOAST yeah TOAST 

now there's no secret to toasting perfection,
there's a dial on the side and you make your selection,
push to the dark or the light and then,
if it pops too soon press down again, 
make toast.

yeah TOAST yeah TOAST 

when the first caveman drove in from the drags,
didn't know what would go with the bacon and the eggs,
must have been a genius got it in his head,
plug the toaster in the wall,
buy a bag of bread,
make toast.

yeah TOAST yeah TOAST

oh wee monsieur bonjour cool cat,
uh huh croissante du bagette,
maurice a vaulzey effeil tower,
o wee maria bagette vouze,

FRENCH TOAST FRENCH TOAST


**HOPE everyone who goes on a fabulous spring break has fun. Myself, I will be stuck in Portland and working. BOOO whatever, at least hutch, ame, math, and stephie will be there : D Board GAMES. haha. Ok I'm out, just gotta get through my last exam and paper due on Thursday ;) LOVE u all. muah.

All I'm gonna say is shopping cart. Wow last night was super fun. Every one was at wilson, it was a great time. Craziness. Sometimes I just get so happy when I think about how lucky I am. Ok, also hidin' in da woods with Drew was super fun. Who does that?! haha. Hope everyone has a great wk end. :D

I'm at work. Again, Blah I know. At least its money I suppose. Last night was a lot of fun. Hutch, Tara, Ame and I went to see Dane Cook. That man is uber uber funny!!! Good times. I love laughing soo much. Then we went back and hung out and watched Saw. Drew got me flowers, nicest ever! Seriously, I never get flowers. I'm still smiling. lol. im so glad i dont wear a retarded helmet too..


Like 7:00 this morning I had to go to an eye appt in PTL. I got these new contacts that like you can wear forever! I can wear them night and day for 30 days. So thats fun. But yeah, then I met with my new Dietetics advisor. Super nice lady. She laid out all I need to do and explained the major to me. I feel a lot better. Except that I have to take BioChem and organic. Um, yuk? YEAH. And I have to take a trillion summer classes which sucks. I just feel like too that I'm going to be so busy for the rest of my college life. That sucks. I just wanna be a lazy bum. But oh well, I guess you have to start being responsible sometime. 

Sunday night I'm going to go see Abby and her babies. I can't wait. I miss her so much, and Ethan and Ella should be almost 6 months now. So excited :D My mom told me today that she wants to go vacation in Aruba now, bc tickets to Hawaii are too expensive. Whateve, anywhere warm would be fine by me. I don't really think I want spring break to come. Minus the schoolwork, I'd rather just stay here..


My days just keep being awesome, and to be honest it kinda scares me..But I'm not gonna complain.. Hope you are all doing awesome. 

much love xoxo <3 <3 <3

Wow. I think I'm gonna give up drinking.. AT least for like 2 weeks i think I can do it. My body might thank me. This morning I woke up on my futon without any blankets in a huge sweatshirt with my contacts in and glasses on also.. Napolean Dynamite was on repeat and he kept saying. GOD. There was 5 pops spilled and a huge 1/2 gallon of Popov just chillin. I went to my computer, and the only IM up was one that was to MYSELF> I actually had a like 10 min long convo with MYSELF. Wow.. SO drunk. It was all giberish and super funny.  Made NO sense. AND i was getting ready for work and burnt my hand on the straightener. SO BAD> But anyways. I had a good night. The night before @ hutchs was fun also. 

I picked a major! YAY. I chose dietetics/ nutrition. I like helping people and i like biology a lot. I figured a nutritionist could be a good job maybe?! who knows we will see. 

Valentines Day is soon. I dont know if im doing ne thing. Everyone is always really sad or really happy. I think its stupid. Who cares? Tonight should be fun though, I think Drew's coming back to State. 

Just went shopping with Dusty and dropped like a lot of unneccesary cash. I made him get these cute shoes too. lol. Money aint no thing.. right? Also- he only bought them b/c the salesman was cute. Thats my boy. haha. 

Have a good Saturday little ones.

Today was the longest day EVER. Bio lab and exam kicked my ass for sure. Oh well. I always do it to myself, with procrastinating to no end. I think it's just how I am. I realized today how lucky I really am. After having a bad day, just talking to Dusty @ work and his wooping laugh, and all my other wonderul friends made me better. Emails and nice calls always make me smile.  I need to take time more often, to stop and just appreciate all I have. My friends for one couldn't be more awesome, my family.. esp my mom, new friends.. It's just all so great and I think I get caught up with school and work or whatever to not realize it. So if you are reading this right now, just know that I love you :) AHH. Sorry I'm done ranting. Goodnight. XOXO

I had a wonderful weekend. Friday night went out with some friends and for some reason decided to get completely hammered. Yeah I need to learn my limits, for sure. But I was awesome at the beer bong I must say. It was fun except when my mom strolls into my dorm room @ 11am and I'm passed out on the futon with all my clothes on and smeared makeup. The first words she said were " Whitney you smell like liquor and beer!!" Glad to make her proud. hah.

Stephanies sister Emily got married. IT was crazy, because I've grown up with them both. After the wedding part, Hutch came over to hang before the reception. OMG did we laugh. I whipped out one of my old journals from like 7th grade. Here's a little sample," Jason Locke loves Becky! NO FAIR. I saw him today and he smiled. So i might ask him out" or "Oh, FYI diary, I am popular now. YAY! I love middle school" or do you remember when we used to say LYLAS? Love ya like a sis? Well apparently i loved my diary and told it, LYLAD. wow. Hutch just shut up! I was definetly a nerd back in the day. BIG nerd. Yeah yeah, im a nerd now, whatever :D But the reception wow, good times for sure. Got to see Ben and Matt from FL which was happy. I miss them! Plus my mom decided to drink and then that she wanted to dance like me. Funny funny night. Sunday night was wonderful also, hung out with Drew again. I think I have a big crush. 

I have to write this ridiculously stupid paper. I started it yesterday but I suck so much at writing. I can't do an outline or I get all frustrated so I just have to sit and start writing. Horrrrrible at it. Oh well!! I'm at work tonite, luckily I dont have to work over 20 hrs this week :D

I got to see Amy last night!!! Freakin yay. Made me super happy. We ate some Panda Express. It was so good to see her. 

A note to Danielle: It's ok to stalk that boy. You are hot enough and also cool. So get er done ok?!

Sorry for the boring post. Have an awesome week everyone. R.I.P Suzie Bouche :(

Sometimes I guess you have to accept that things are good and thats it. I have to get over the fact that if there is nothing negative about a situation in my life thats ok. I can't expect the worst, or hold myself back from something awesome because I'm afraid it might not be later on. MY D, Jor, and Rach are amazing. And chucking that "box" at me last night made me laugh a lot. Laughing is so awesome, and I swear makes everything better. Honestly though, its super refreshing to meet new people who actually seem to be completely sincere. Its a really weird feeling for me, but so good. And I'm gonna take it for all its worth. I'm on like 3 hours of sleep and my eye sockets hurt like a mofo. But not gonna lie, I love talking for hours at night.I do hate waking up though and having to leave.

I have a million things to do for next week. I have a wedding and work this weekend. And a paper, and a ton of bio stuff to do by Monday. But who cares? It always seems like life is busy so I should just accept it and shut up! (As Napolean would say)

My new goal for the month, well besides finally picking a MAJOR, is to stop swearing. Or at least not so much. As Danielle put it, using the F-word in every sentence makes me sound like a trailer slut. :D.. hey that might not be SO bad..

But really I have no idea why I keep procrastinating the whole major thing. Coming into college I swear I knew everything I wanted and exactly how I would get there. But for some reason suddenly the word "doctor" isn't doing as much for me as it used to.. So,any suggestions would be amazing. It seems so weird that we go to school for SO long, what for? So we can get a job, a house, a family, have kids and pay for them to do exactly what we did.. Sometimes it all seems fucked up and routine.

Anyways, gonna go try and read this IAH before I fall asleep at work..

"Theres something about you,
Tears me inside out whenever you're around
There's something about you
Speeding through my veins until we hit the ground
And there's something about this rush
Take it away
It made me feel so good
I get a feeling, you get a feeling, we got a feeling
Like we could die

we just cant get enough
we just cant get enough
oh, it's amazing..

Theres something about you
That tears me inside out whenever you're around
And theres something about you
That makes me fly
You're a heart attack, just the kind I like
and there's something about your kiss
haunting and strange
That makes me feel so good
I get a feeling, you get a feeling we got a feeling
Like we're alive"


Sometimes its weird to think about the way things happen and when they do. It's almost like things are supposed to happen for some reason, but you can't figure out why.

So its Monday, I'm at work again. BOO. It never ends!! Oh well, at least we didn't have classes today. My wk end completely rocked. I got to see all my friends and hangout with really cool people. 

Thursday- We all went to Sparty's and danced forever. There was like 10 of us in the car on the way over, including Amy and Ron in the trunk. hah. Jake was beyond drunk. And there was this guy who was dancing so crazy, it was awesome.
Friday- I went with Danielle, Jor, and their cousin Dave among others to this coffee shop. There was a band called Sea defeats Sparrow playing. It was really fun. Then we chilled @ Beth's. I played euchre with some boys and totally didn't win. Dave is adorable, he's 16 and is really funny. It was like having a little brother stay with us all wk end. I always wanted a brother.
Saturday- Drew from my CJ class came to hang out in the dorm with me. ;) He seems really super awesome. Everyone was hanging out on the floor that night. His friend Andrew came to chill too. So we drank. Best ever, my RA got wasted!! He was going around and knocking on  peoples doors to ask for ID, and then like stumbling over. SO funny. 
Sunday- I went to Hutch's dorm and hung out with a bunch of people that I haven't saw in a long time.
